603
00:35:29,760 --> 00:35:31,010
Mr. Snake, you're here.

604
00:35:31,990 --> 00:35:32,740
Please, have a seat.

605
00:35:34,430 --> 00:35:36,450
Mr. Snake, I wanted to ask you something.

606
00:35:37,240 --> 00:35:39,090
You've been with Grandmaster for so long.

607
00:35:39,360 --> 00:35:40,820
You must know his likes and dislikes.

608
00:35:41,510 --> 00:35:43,660
How would one go about pleasing him?

609
00:35:57,030 --> 00:35:59,370
Grandmaster, look at this table.

610
00:35:59,390 --> 00:36:00,780
I polished it until it shines.

611
00:36:05,110 --> 00:36:05,970
And the floor,

612
00:36:07,160 --> 00:36:08,530
not a speck of dust.

613
00:36:12,880 --> 00:36:14,300
What do you want from me today?

614
00:36:21,240 --> 00:36:23,380
Last night my stomach hurt again.

615
00:36:23,680 --> 00:36:25,240
It hurt so much I thought I would die.

616
00:36:25,620 --> 00:36:28,890
Didn't you save me with your blood last time?

617
00:36:30,910 --> 00:36:31,820
What do you want?

618
00:36:32,760 --> 00:36:33,860
I want you on call.

619
00:36:33,880 --> 00:36:34,780
To donate blood for free.

620
00:36:35,990 --> 00:36:36,970
I just mean,

621
00:36:37,390 --> 00:36:38,700
from now on, could you use

622
00:36:38,720 --> 00:36:40,090
your precious and treasured blood

623
00:36:40,470 --> 00:36:42,220
to save me in time when I'm in trouble?

624
00:36:42,760 --> 00:36:44,220
After all, this little body of mine

625
00:36:44,800 --> 00:36:46,220
can still be useful to you.

626
00:36:46,990 --> 00:36:48,570
We can help each other, right?

627
00:37:02,880 --> 00:37:04,140
You're bargaining with me.

628
00:37:09,430 --> 00:37:10,300
I wouldn't dare.

629
00:37:12,110 --> 00:37:13,220
It's a plea.

630
00:37:14,280 --> 00:37:15,340
You want my blood?

631
00:37:17,200 --> 00:37:18,050
It depends on my mood.

632
00:37:19,470 --> 00:37:21,340
So what would put you in a good mood?

633
00:37:25,680 --> 00:37:27,180
You poor thing,

634
00:37:27,200 --> 00:37:28,450
you even have to think about that?

635
00:37:44,360 --> 00:37:44,930
Kill.

636
00:37:47,240 --> 00:37:48,370
Kill someone for me.

637
00:37:49,110 --> 00:37:50,700
Isn't that a bit above my pay grade?

638
00:37:57,640 --> 00:37:58,890
Grandmaster, don't leave.

639
00:38:01,720 --> 00:38:02,410
Just wait.

640
00:38:03,360 --> 00:38:05,450
I'll find out what else you need.

641
00:38:10,160 --> 00:38:12,010
Grandmaster.

642
00:38:13,760 --> 00:38:15,220
You've worked hard all morning.

643
00:38:15,390 --> 00:38:16,530
Let me serve you.

644
00:38:17,550 --> 00:38:19,140
I heard you have trouble sleeping.

645
00:38:19,160 --> 00:38:21,010
From my years of work experience,

646
00:38:21,240 --> 00:38:23,410
it's most likely caused by too much worry and stress.

647
00:38:26,390 --> 00:38:27,090
Mr. Snake.

648
00:38:27,760 --> 00:38:29,740
So what would make Grandmaster happy?

649
00:38:33,200 --> 00:38:34,820
Grandmaster likes pillows?

650
00:38:39,390 --> 00:38:40,490
He can't sleep well?

651
00:38:40,680 --> 00:38:41,570
He can't fall asleep?

652
00:38:44,030 --> 00:38:44,530
Ridiculous.

653
00:38:44,910 --> 00:38:46,490
What could possibly trouble me?

654
00:38:48,110 --> 00:38:50,490
